  <purpose>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_executing_system__artifact_definition&quot;&#xD;
name=&quot;XE_executing_system__artifact_definition&quot;>&lt;/a>&lt;a id=&quot;Purpose&quot; name=&quot;Purpose&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of an evolving Executing System is to have something built that is concrete and executable so users,&#xD;
    implementers, managers, and other affected stakeholders can touch and feel.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    An instance of the Executing System aids in developing a shared vision of the proposed solution and provides a means&#xD;
    for understanding the features of the selected COTS Package(s), user business processes, and the user business process&#xD;
    interactions within the solution. It orients the project toward identification and resolution of critical issues and&#xD;
    risks rather than the production of paper documents.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    An instance of the Executing System stimulates early discovery of mismatches and negotiations to resolve the mismatches&#xD;
    within the operational context of the system (e.g., use cases). It also objectively demonstrates the current state of&#xD;
    the project. This acts as a forcing function that drives the project to gain closure at regular intervals. Development&#xD;
    of an instance of the Executing System also fosters early elimination of architectural defects.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
